			<td class="subhead">Rory&nbsp;Stear</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td><b>Founder, Chairman and CEO,&nbsp;Freeplay Energy</b></td>
		</tr>
		
		
		<tr>
			<td><br><img src=/shared_files/techspeakers_photos/Stear_Rory.jpg align=left valign="top">&nbsp;Rory Stear, Executive Chairman of Freeplay Energy plc, is a South African born "serial entrepreneur" who worked in business development, mergers and acquisitions, prior to co-founding Freeplay Energy Group in 1994.  Since it’s founding, Freeplay has become a role model for corporate social responsibility and has been showcased in the Agenda issue of Fast Company magazine and in numerous other global publications.  Mr. Stear founded the Freeplay Foundation in 1998, which has become a highly respected, award winning international non-profit social enterprise. <br><br> 
 
Mr. Stear was one of the first South Africans invited to join the African Business Roundtable (1995).  In 1996 he was a member of President Nelson Mandela's business delegation to the UK and again travelled with the President on his 1998 visit to the USA.  He is the recipient of numerous business awards, including the Theodor Herzl Award.  He serves on the Deans Council at the Kennedy School of Government at Harvard and on the board of the Business School at Nelson Mandela University. He is a member of YPO and a fellow of the Schwab Foundation for Social Entrepreneurship. In 2007 he was named a CNN/Fortune/Time “Principal Voice”. In October 2007 he, in partnership with his wife Kristine Pearson who heads the Freeplay Foundation, were named one of Time’s Global Eco Heroes.
</td>
		
		
